selector.name: addClass()
selector.description: Adds one or more class names to selected elements

selector.name: after()
selector.description: Inserts content after selected elements

selector.name: append()
selector.description: Inserts content at the end of selected elements

selector.name: appendTo()
selector.description: Inserts HTML elements at the end of selected elements

selector.name: attr()
selector.description: Sets or returns attributes/values of selected elements

selector.name: before()
selector.description: Inserts content before selected elements

selector.name: clone()
selector.description: Makes a copy of selected elements

selector.name: css()
selector.description: Sets or returns one or more style properties for selected elements

selector.name: detach()
selector.description: Removes selected elements (keeps data and events)

selector.name: empty()
selector.description: Removes all child nodes and content from selected elements

selector.name: hasClass()
selector.description: Checks if any of the selected elements have a specified class name

selector.name: height()
selector.description: Sets or returns the height of selected elements

selector.name: html()
selector.description: Sets or returns the content of selected elements

selector.name: innerHeight()
selector.description: Returns the height of an element (includes padding, but not border)

selector.name: innerWidth()
selector.description: Returns the width of an element (includes padding, but not border)

selector.name: insertAfter()
selector.description: Inserts HTML elements after selected elements

selector.name: insertBefore()
selector.description: Inserts HTML elements before selected elements

selector.name: offset()
selector.description: Sets or returns the offset coordinates for selected elements (relative to the document)

selector.name: offsetParent()
selector.description: Returns the first positioned parent element

selector.name: outerHeight()
selector.description: Returns the height of an element (includes padding and border)

selector.name: outerWidth()
selector.description: Returns the width of an element (includes padding and border)

selector.name: position()
selector.description: Returns the position (relative to the parent element) of an element

selector.name: prepend()
selector.description: Inserts content at the beginning of selected elements

selector.name: prependTo()
selector.description: Inserts HTML elements at the beginning of selected elements

selector.name: prop()
selector.description: Sets or returns properties/values of selected elements

selector.name: remove()
selector.description: Removes the selected elements (including data and events)

selector.name: removeAttr()
selector.description: Removes one or more attributes from selected elements

selector.name: removeClass()
selector.description: Removes one or more classes from selected elements

selector.name: removeProp()
selector.description: Removes a property set by the prop() method

selector.name: replaceAll()
selector.description: Replaces selected elements with new HTML elements

selector.name: replaceWith()
selector.description: Replaces selected elements with new content

selector.name: scrollLeft()
selector.description: Sets or returns the horizontal scrollbar position of selected elements

selector.name: scrollTop()
selector.description: Sets or returns the vertical scrollbar position of selected elements

selector.name: text()
selector.description: Sets or returns the text content of selected elements

selector.name: toggleClass()
selector.description: Toggles between adding/removing one or more classes from selected elements

selector.name: unwrap()
selector.description: Removes the parent element of the selected elements

selector.name: val()
selector.description: Sets or returns the value attribute of the selected elements (for form elements)

selector.name: width()
selector.description: Sets or returns the width of selected elements

selector.name: wrap()
selector.description: Wraps HTML element(s) around each selected element

selector.name: wrapAll()
selector.description: Wraps HTML element(s) around all selected elements

selector.name: wrapInner()
selector.description: Wraps HTML element(s) around the content of each selected element
